com.ericsson.oss.itpf.datalayer.dps.bucket.spi

Interface ObjectManager


  • public interface ObjectManager
    Defines the capabilities of a class which can be used to create or destroy persistently backed DPS objects.

        DecoratedPersistenceObject createPersistenceObject(java.lang.String namespace,
                                                   java.lang.String type,
                                                   java.lang.String version,
                                                   java.lang.String bucketName,
                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> additionalParameters)
                                            throws NotPossibleToCreateEntityException,
                                                   UnknownTypeException
        Create a new persistence object with the given data.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the namespace of the type of persistence object to be created.
        type - the type of the object required.
        version - the version of the object to be created. Can be null which signifies that the latest version should be created.
        bucketName - the name of the data bucket into which the object should be created.
        additionalParameters - map that may be used to pass additional parameters.
        Returns:
        the newly created persistence object.
        Throws:
        NotPossibleToCreateEntityException - if the data supplied to create a new persistent entity cannot be used to create an entity known to this system
        UnknownTypeException - if the data supplied to create a new managed entity represents an unknown entity to this system.

      • createRootManagedObject

        DecoratedManagedObject createRootManagedObject(java.lang.String namespace,
                                               java.lang.String type,
                                               java.lang.String version,
                                               java.lang.String name,
                                               java.lang.String bucketName,
                                               DecoratedManagedObject parent,
                                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> attributeMap)
                                        throws NotPossibleToCreateEntityException,
                                               UnknownTypeException
        Create a managed object that is a MIB root with the supplied data.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the namespace of the type of managed object to be created.
        type - the type of the object to be created.
        version - the version of the object to be created. Can be null which signifies that the latest version should be created.
        name - the name of the object to be created.
        bucketName - the name of the data bucket into which the object should be created.
        parent - the parent of the managed object. Can be null.
        attributeMap - the attributes (name, value) of the managed object. The implementation of object manager should NOT set these attributes on the object being created.
        Returns:
        the newly created root managed object
        Throws:
        IllegalParentException - if there is any error relating to the parent of this managed object
        NotPossibleToCreateEntityException - if the data supplied to create a new managed entity cannot be used to create an entity known to this system
        UnknownTypeException - if the data supplied to create a new managed entity represents an unknown entity to this system.

      • createManagedObject

        DecoratedManagedObject createManagedObject(java.lang.String type,
                                           java.lang.String name,
                                           java.lang.String bucketName,
                                           DecoratedManagedObject parent,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> attributeMap)
                                    throws NotPossibleToCreateEntityException,
                                           UnknownTypeException
        Create a (non-root) managed object with the supplied data.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of the new managed object.
        name - the name of the new managed object, may be null.
        bucketName - the name of the data bucket into which the object should be created.
        parent - the parent of the new managed object.
        attributeMap - the attributes (name, value) of the managed object. The implementation of object manager should NOT set these attributes on the object being created.
        Returns:
        a newly created, and persisted managed object.
        Throws:
        IllegalParentException - if there is any error relating to the parent of this managed object
        NotPossibleToCreateEntityException - if the data supplied to create a new managed entity cannot be used to create an entity known to this system
        UnknownTypeException - if the data supplied to create a new managed entity represents an unknown entity to this system.

      • postCreate

        void postCreate(DecoratedPersistenceObject objectBeingCreated,
                boolean successful,
                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> additionalParameters)
        Creation of the specified object has been completed.

        This method will always be called before the object has been passed back to a DPS user.

        Parameters:
        objectBeingCreated - the object which has just been created.
        successful - indication of whether the creation was successful or not. If not successful then steps should be taken to undo the object's creation in the respective layers.
        additionalParameters - map that may be used to pass additional parameters.

      • copyManagedObject

        DecoratedManagedObject copyManagedObject(DecoratedManagedObject objectToCopy,
                                         DecoratedManagedObject parent,
                                         java.lang.String destinationBucketName,
                                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> additionalParameters)
        Copies a managed object into a bucket. All attributes and basic object properties will be copied.

        This method can be used to copy any managed object, regardless of if the object in question is a true root, a mib root with a parent, or a normal managed object.

        Parameters:
        objectToCopy - the managed object that is to be copied
        parent - the managed object that will be the parent of the newly copied object. Should be null if the object being copied has no parent
        destinationBucketName - the name of the bucket to copy the object into
        additionalParameters - map that may be used to pass additional parameters.
        Returns:
        the copied managed object, which will be a child of the supplied parent (if appropriate).
